name: Takemiya Masaki Kudan no Igo Taishou
overview: Another obscure Go game developed by an unknown contract developer. Promoted with the image of Masaki Takemiya, a professional player who is himself a 9th-Dan (the highest standard rank in Go) and who frequently won competitions throughout the 1980s and 1990s. The game features a number of CPU opponents - indicated with portraits - of increasing difficulty, including Takemiya himself.
